sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1767009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: P(Lac)IQ RBS Aiia RBS LuxR ter ter luxpR RBS eyfp ter ter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
We designed and built a kill switch mechanism that based on the activation of a lethal gene downstream of an inducible promoter that can be activated over time.

In order to understand our system we started to test the first part of our genetic circuit , to test it we built the first part ( k1767001 ) driving expression of florescence protein .

The here presented BioBrick consists of a constitutive promoter(I14032) driving expression of LuxR followed by a Lux promoter (R0062) , driving expression of YFP.

The idea is to retrieve information about the expression of a fluorescent reporter downstream of the pLuxR promoter in absence and increasing concentrations of AHL.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1767001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: P(Lac)IQ RBS Aiia RBS LuxR term term luxpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We designed and built a kill switch mechanism that is based on the activation of a lethal gene downstream of an inducible promoter that is activated over time. The presented part is the first module of our designed genetic circuit (BBa_K1767003). In order to characterize and understand each module of the genetic circuit we designed two composite parts that allow us to verify the (1) the degradation rate of AHL by AiiA and (2) induction of the pLux promoter by LuxR in presence of AHL with and without co-expression of AiiA. (1) The here presented BioBrick consists of a constitutive promoter driving expression of AiiA and LuxR followed by a Lux promoter which drives expression of a fluorescent reporter (here: yellow fluorescent protein). sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
